snippet.textDisplay:
Song Explanation: 
Gotilo(Gujarati) Means "FIND HIM"

"Gotilo" is a song about searching for an adventurous sailor. The lyrics talk about finding someone who loves exploring the sea with passion and bravery, not just sticking to the usual shores. The singer wants to discover a seafarer who seeks excitement and isn't satisfied with the ordinary. The song describes the journey from the shore to the deep sea, representing the pursuit of thrilling experiences. The chorus repeats the call to find such a spirited sailor and encourages the spirit of exploration. The lyrics metaphorically depict the sea as a metaphor for life's journey, where one must navigate through both calm shores and turbulent waters. The chorus(Female Singers) emphasizes the search for this fearless seafarer, urging them to find their purpose and stay resilient amidst the storms.

In Hindi:
"Gotilo" ye gaana hai jo ek joshila aur adventurous sailor dhoondhne ko keh raha hai. Lyrics vyakti karte hain ki koi aisa dhundhe jo samundar mein utsaah aur bahaduri ke saath ghoomna pasand karta ho, sirf aam kinaron se kahin nahi rukna chahta. Gayak ek aise sailor ko khojne ka ichha vyakt karta hai jo utsahit anubhavon ki talash mein hai aur samanya se santusht nahi hai. Gaana kinare se gehre samundar tak ka safar describe karta hai, jo mahatvapurn anubhavon ki talash ko darshata hai. Chorus bar-bar ek aise jazbaat bhare sailor ko dhoondhne ka aagrah karta hai aur anveshan ki bhavana ko badhava deta hai.


Artist: 
Aditya Gadhvi is a playback singer and lyricist from Gujarat, India. He has rendered numerous chart-topping songs in various Indian languages and is involved in Gujarati film scoring.

To those who can't understand: 
Gotilo (In English)

find him, O find him
In the joy that's not found,
In the empty flags of vanity,
Find me a zealous seafarer.

Go from the shore to the shallows,
And from shallows to the sea,
Go, find him, O find him,
In the journey of a passionate seafarer.

Go from the shore to the shallows,
Find him, O find him.

Let us flow where we're flowing,
Let us stay where we are,
Let us flow, let us flow,
Let us stay, stay where we are.

One who isn't pleased,
With flags of vanity,
O find me such a zealous seafarer.

Tell me who could be such a sailor man,
Tell me his name and address,
O find me such a zealous seafarer.

O sailor man, yo-ho! Heave-ho!
Take your boat and go!
O sailor man, yo-ho! Heave-ho!
Take your boat and go!

In the depth of your mind,
Take a dive and find,
The priceless pearl of your soul,
O find me such a zealous seafarer.

One who won't seek what is sought,
And won't search what is found,
O find me such a zealous seafarer.

And you must confront the ocean,
Because on the shores, only footprints remain,
And castles made of sand.

When the thunderstorms pounce,
And the paddles start to pant,
Even then, one who stays the course,
With courage and will.

O find me such a zealous seafarer,
O find me such a zealous seafarer.



Keep listening! 😇🎶🎵
